{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T04:52:10.393Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Feature scaling"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is a preprocessing technique used to "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "normalize the range of independent variables (features)"}, {"type": "text", "text": " so that all features contribute proportionately to model learning, preventing features with larger magnitudes from dominating the model simply due to their scale."}]}, {"type": "blockquote", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Simple definition:"}, {"type": "text", "text": " \"Feature scaling is a technique used to normalize the range of independent variables so that no single feature dominates the others due to its magnitude. It helps machine learning models interpret all features on an equal footing.\""}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Feature Scaling — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why feature scaling matters"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When your dataset contains features with "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "vastly different ranges"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", algorithms that rely on "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "distance calculations"}, {"type": "text", "text": " or "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "gradient-based optimization"}, {"type": "text", "text": " will be biased toward larger-scale features."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Example problem"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- Feature A: Age (0–100)\n- Feature B: Income (0–1,000,000)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Without scaling, the model will treat income as "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "10,000× more important"}, {"type": "text", "text": " simply because of its larger numbers."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key benefits of feature scaling"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Benefit"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Description"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Improves model accuracy"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Features on the same scale help models learn faster and more accurately"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Speeds up training"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Gradient descent converges quicker when data is scaled properly"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Ensures fairness"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "No feature gets more \"weight\" just because it has bigger numbers"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Makes visualization easier"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Scaled features fit better in graphs and heatmaps"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Enables regularization"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Regularization penalizes coefficients appropriately when features are scaled"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When to use feature scaling"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "✅ "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Scale your data when using:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Algorithm Type"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why scaling is needed"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Distance-based"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (KNN, SVM, Clustering)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Euclidean distance is affected by magnitude differences"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Gradient-based"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (Linear/Logistic Regression, Neural Networks)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Gradient descent converges faster"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Regularization"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (Ridge, Lasso)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Coefficients penalized appropriately"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "PCA"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Principal components computed based on variance"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "❌ "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Don't scale when using:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Algorithm"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why scaling isn't needed"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Tree-based"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (Random Forest, XGBoost, Decision Trees)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Trees split based on thresholds, not distances"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Two main types of feature scaling"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Standardization (Z-score Normalization)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Transforms data to have "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Mean = 0"}, {"type": "text", "text": " and "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Standard Deviation = 1"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Formula"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n\\[\nx' = \\frac{x - \\bar{x}}{\\sigma}\n\\]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Where:\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "x"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = original value\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\bar{x}"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = mean of feature\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\sigma"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = standard deviation"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Characteristics"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- Mean becomes "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "0"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\n- About "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "68%"}, {"type": "text", "text": " of values lie between "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "-1 and 1"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\n- Does "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "not"}, {"type": "text", "text": " bound values to a fixed range (can be negative or >1)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "When to use"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- Data follows "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Gaussian (normal) distribution"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Outliers"}, {"type": "text", "text": " are present (less sensitive than Min-Max)\n- Most common default choice for ML algorithms"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Normalization (Min-Max Scaling)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Rescales all values to a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "fixed range"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", usually "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "italic"}, {"type": "italic"}], "text": "."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Formula"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n\\[\nx' = \\frac{x - \\text{min}(x)}{\\text{max}(x) - \\text{min}(x)}\n\\]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Where:\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "x"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = original value\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\text{min}(x)"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = minimum value\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\text{max}(x)"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = maximum value"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Characteristics"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- Preserves the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "shape of the dataset"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (no distortion)\n- Bounds values to "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "italic"}, {"type": "italic"}], "text": " (or [-1, 1] if desired)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "When to use"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- You know "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "minimum and maximum bounds"}, {"type": "text", "text": " of data\n- All features should have "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "equal importance"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\n- First scaler choice to transform a feature\n- Neural networks often prefer range"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Other scaling methods"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "3. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Robust Scaling"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Designed to be "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "robust to outliers"}, {"type": "text", "text": " by using median and interquartile range (IQR) instead of mean and standard deviation."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Formula"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n\\[\nx' = \\frac{x - Q_2(x)}{Q_3(x) - Q_1(x)}\n\\]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Where:\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "Q_1"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = 25th percentile (1st quartile)\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "Q_2"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = 50th percentile (median)\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "Q_3"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = 75th percentile (3rd quartile)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "ICR (Interquartile Range)"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "Q_3 - Q_1"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = range from 25% to 75%"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "When to use"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- Data has "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "significant outliers"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\n- Other scaling methods don't work effectively with outliers"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "4. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Unit Vector Normalization"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Treats each data point as a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "vector"}, {"type": "text", "text": " and divides by its norm to get a unit vector."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Formula"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n\\[\nx' = \\frac{x}{\\|x\\|}\n\\]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common norms: "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "L1 norm"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (sum of absolute values) or "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "L2 norm"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (Euclidean length)."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "When to use"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Text classification, document similarity (where direction matters more than magnitude)."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Implementation in scikit-learn"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "StandardScaler (Standardization)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\nimport numpy as np\n\nX = np.array([[100], [200], [300], [400], [500]])\n\nscaler = StandardScaler()\nX_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X)\n\nprint(f\"Mean: {X_scaled.mean():.3f}\")  # ~0\nprint(f\"Std: {X_scaled.std():.3f}\")    # ~1"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "MinMaxScaler (Normalization)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from sklearn.preprocessing import MinMaxScaler\n\nX = np.array([[100], [200], [300], [400], [500]])\n\nscaler = MinMaxScaler()\nX_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X)\n\nprint(f\"Min: {X_scaled.min():.3f}\")  # 0.0\nprint(f\"Max: {X_scaled.max():.3f}\")  # 1.0"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "RobustScaler (Robust to outliers)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from sklearn.preprocessing import RobustScaler\n\nX = np.array([[100], [200], [300], [1000]])  # 1000 is outlier\n\nscaler = RobustScaler()\nX_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X)\n\nprint(X_scaled)"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Standardization vs Normalization comparison"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Aspect"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Standardization (Z-score)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Normalization (Min-Max)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Result range"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "No fixed range (can be negative or >1)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Fixed range or [-1, 1]"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Mean"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "0"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Between 0 and 1"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Std Dev"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Depends on data"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Outlier sensitivity"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Less sensitive"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "More sensitive (outliers compress other values)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Best for"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Gaussian distribution, outliers present"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Known bounds, equal feature importance"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Preserves shape"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "No (distorts distribution)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Yes (no distortion)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Common algorithms"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "SVM, Logistic Regression, PCA"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Neural Networks, KNN"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Best practices for feature scaling"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "✅ "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Scale train and test separately"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# WRONG: Fit on all data\nscaler = StandardScaler()\nX_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X)  # Including test!\n\n# CORRECT: Fit on train only\nscaler = StandardScaler()\nX_train_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X_train)  # Fit on train\nX_test_scaled = scaler.transform(X_test)         # Transform test"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Why"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Prevents data leakage (test data shouldn't influence scaling parameters)."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "✅ "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Use Pipeline for reproducibility"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from sklearn.pipeline import Pipeline\nfrom sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\nfrom sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\n\npipeline = Pipeline([\n    ('scaler', StandardScaler()),\n    ('model', LogisticRegression())\n])\n\npipeline.fit(X_train, y_train)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Benefits"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Ensures scaling is applied consistently during training and prediction."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "✅ "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Check for outliers first"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "If outliers present → use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "RobustScaler"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "If no outliers → use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "StandardScaler"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (default)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "✅ "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Don't scale categorical features"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Only apply scaling to "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "numerical features"}, {"type": "text", "text": "; categorical features should be encoded (e.g., one-hot encoding) but not scaled."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key takeaways"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Feature scaling"}, {"type": "text", "text": " normalizes feature ranges so no single feature dominates due to magnitude, ensuring all features contribute proportionately to model learning."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Critical for"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Distance-based algorithms (KNN, SVM, Clustering), gradient-based optimization (Linear Regression, Neural Networks), regularization, PCA."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Not needed for"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Tree-based models (Random Forest, XGBoost)."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Standardization (Z-score)"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Mean = 0, Std = 1; best for Gaussian distribution or outliers present; no fixed range."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Normalization (Min-Max)"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Range; preserves data shape; best when bounds are known; use as first scaler choice."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Robust Scaling"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Uses median and IQR; designed for outliers; less sensitive than other methods."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Best practice"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Fit scaler on "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "train only"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", then transform test; use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Pipeline"}, {"type": "text", "text": " for consistency; check for outliers first; don't scale categorical features."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Benefits"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Improves accuracy, speeds up training (faster gradient descent), ensures fairness among features, enables proper regularization."}]}]}]}]}}